, 1279.7, 1141.7, 1302.8]}, {"text": "Net written premiums for personal auto increased in 2013 and 2012, with both years reflecting rate increases", "bbox": [104.2, 1352.5, 1110.4, 1375.8]}, {"text": "in recent years, ongoing high levels of policy retention, premium growth initiatives and a higher level of", "bbox": [104.2, 1377.5, 1051.3, 1400.8]}, {"text": "insured exposures.", "bbox": [104.2, 1402.5, 280.2, 1425.8]}, {"text": "The 2013 total loss and loss expense ratio rose 4.1 percentage points, largely due to a 4.3 point reduction in the", "bbox": [104.2, 1452.5, 1140.6, 1475.8]}, {"text": "ratio for favorable reserve development on prior accident years. That reduction related to both case and IBNR", "bbox": [104.2, 1477.5, 1118.2, 1500.8]}, {"text": "reserves. For accident year 2013, a lower catastrophe loss and loss expenses ratio offset a modest increase in the", "bbox": [104.2, 1502.5, 1164.5, 1525.8]}]}